##The smallest healer in Hubei is discharged from hospital!

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter, Deng Yafei, intern, Chen Zijia, correspondent, Li Yi, Fan Shuai, Jiang Hui

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xiao Bao, aged 9 months, was discharged from the Dongfeng General Hospital in Shiyan City. All pictures in this article are from Dongfeng General Hospital

At 11:00 am on February 11, Xiao Bao (not his real name) , who was only 9 months old, was discharged from Dongfeng General Hospital in Shiyan City. This is the youngest case of newly diagnosed pneumonia in Hubei Province.

On January 27, Xiao Bao's father was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia at the Dongfeng General Hospital in Shiyan, where he was subsequently diagnosed.

"At the time of admission, in addition to the infection of new coronavirus, the child was also infected with Mycoplasma pneumoniae infection and influenza B infection. At the same time, there was a decrease in granulocytes, which could easily be combined with bacterial infection. The child was very vulnerable to the impairment of multiple organ functions throughout the body, and the situation was very critical, " said Chen Quanjing, director of the Department of Pediatrics at Dongfeng General Hospital, a Chinese Medicine Hospital.

In response to Xiao Bao's condition, Dongfeng General Hospital of Shiyan and Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital Paediatricians immediately discussed and formulated a treatment plan. After 15 days of treatment, Xiao Bao's indexes were stable and both nucleic acid tests were negative.

On February 11, Xiao Bao and his son were released from the hospital together. Before his father was released from the hospital, he said, "Chen, director of the Department of Pediatrics and Jiang, director of the Department of infection, are very careful and carefully treated. The child's condition is getting better and better. Now he is completely well and can go home. I am so happy! "

Infant presenting with dyspnea and Hypoxia

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The hospital experts discussed the plan of treatment.

"because the child is breathing rapidly, breathing difficulties, hypoxia situation, coupled with young age, weak resistance, the child's condition was very dangerous, " Chen said.

After admitting Xiao Bao, the hospital immediately arranged the pediatric medical team to be admitted to the isolation ward and organized expert consultation. During the course of treatment, the hospital contacted the paediatrician of Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital to analyze and guide Xiao Bao's condition and participate in the formulation of treatment plan.

"In the case of the child, we have strong anti-bacterial, anti-viral, anti-mycoplasma, oxygen therapy, and supportive treatment with Gamma Globulin to help the child raise antibodies, neutralize toxins, and clear the virus. Eventually, the child's condition began to improve,"Chen said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The medical staff took care of Xiao Bao.

After 15 days of treatment, he was discharged

"after 15 days of intensive treatment and care, Xiao Bao's mental state, feeding and other aspects are good, breathing, heart rate and other indicators are very stable, " Chen said.

It is understood that Xiao Bao's two nucleic acid tests before discharge were negative, lung CT showed inflammation absorption, liver function, myocardial damage has also recovered, in line with the discharge criteria. Xiao Bao's father also met the discharge criteria as early as February 7, and both nucleic acid tests were negative.

On the day of discharge, Chen Quanjing detailed explained the matters needing attention after discharge, contact the hospital 120 ambulance sent father and son home smoothly. When they returned home, they were placed in isolation for another two weeks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The paramedics took Xiao Bao and his father.

Xiao Bao's father told reporters, "Doctors and nurses are working very hard, it's not easy, working in protective clothing for so long, sometimes you almost fainted, and still taking care of us, I really appreciate it. Hospital food is also good, three meat one vegetable soup. There's hot water in the ward. Chen, director of the Department of Pediatrics and Jiang, director of the Department of Infectious Diseases, worked very hard and treated carefully. The child's condition is getting better and better. Now he is completely well. He can go home. I am so happy!"

Li Xingwang, a member of the National Medical Expert Group and chief expert of the Infectious Disease Diagnosis and Research Center of Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing, said at a news conference held by the National Health Commission on Feb. 4 that based on the available case data, the youngest reported age is one month and the oldest is in their 90s, so the population is generally susceptible."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The medical staff treating Xiao Bao took a photo with his father and son.
